---
id: org.dxos.plugin.blogger
name: BloggerPlugin
version: 0.1.0
---

A Composer plugin for authoring blog posts with agent assistance. An author
organises work into **Publications** (a named collection with shared base
agent instructions) that contain **Posts**. Each Post has a planning
**outline** and one or more **Drafts** (versions), each an independently
commentable markdown document.

The plugin also defines a provider-agnostic **publisher** capability contract
(`PublisherService`) and the push/pull sync operations that consume it.
`plugin-typefully` is the first implementation, authenticating via a
`plugin-connector` `Connection`.

## Extensions

The following extension dialects are used in this document.
Each extension is defined in the Appendix or resolved via its URI.

| Term        | URI                            |
|-------------|--------------------------------|
| `type`      | `org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0`       |
| `feat`      | `org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0`       |
| `test`      | `org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0`       |
| `component` | `org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0`  |
| `op`        | `org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0`         |
| `service`   | `org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0`    |

### Existing types used by this plugin

| Type                 | Source                     | Notes                                                                 |
| -------------------- | --------------------------- | ---------------------------------------------------------------------- |
| `Markdown.Document`  | `@dxos/plugin-markdown`    | Backs `instructions`, `outline`, and every `Draft.content`.           |
| `Connection`         | `@dxos/plugin-connector`   | Provider-neutral credential handle passed to every `PublisherService` call. |

## Types

```mdl
type Draft
  desc: >
    A single version of a Post; wraps a commentable markdown document.
    `label` defaults to "Draft N" (N = 1-based position at creation).
  typename: org.dxos.type.blogger.draft
  fields:
    label?: string
    createdAt?: string             # ISO 8601 timestamp
    content: Ref<Markdown.Document>
  annotations:
    label: [label]
```

```mdl
type Post
  desc: >
    A blog post: a planning outline plus one or more ordered Drafts
    (versions). `summary` is shown on PostCard; the newest Draft (last in
    the array) is selected by default in PostArticle.
  typename: org.dxos.type.blogger.post
  fields:
    name?: string
    summary?: string                # shown on PostCard
    outline: Ref<Markdown.Document>
    drafts?: Ref<Draft>[]           # order = version order
  annotations:
    icon: ph--article--regular
    hue: amber
    label: [name]
```

```mdl
type Publication
  desc: >
    A named collection of Posts carrying shared base instructions for the
    assistant agent.
  typename: org.dxos.type.blogger.publication
  fields:
    name?: string
    instructions: Ref<Markdown.Document>  # base agent instructions
    posts?: Ref<Post>[]
  annotations:
    icon: ph--books--regular
    hue: amber
    label: [name]
```

```mdl
type PublisherDraft
  desc: >
    Provider-neutral draft DTO exchanged across the PublisherService
    boundary. A plain Effect Schema.Struct — NOT an ECHO object.
  fields:
    id: string
    text: string
    title?: string
    status?: string
    scheduledAt?: string
    url?: string
```

```mdl
type PublisherDraftInput
  desc: Input shape for PublisherService.createDraft / updateDraft.
  fields:
    text: string
    title?: string
    scheduledAt?: string
```

## Components

```mdl
component PublicationArticle
  desc: >
    Article surface for a Publication (AppSurface.object(Article,
    Publication)). A toolbar toggle swaps between two view modes: `gallery`
    (default) — a Masonry grid of PostCard tiles, one per `subject.posts` —
    and `instructions` — the Publication's shared instructions document,
    embedded via the markdown article Surface. Toolbar also carries a
    `+ Post` action.
  props:
    role: string
    attendableId: string
    subject: Publication
  state:
    mode: gallery | instructions
  actions:
    toggleView()
    addPost()
    openPost(post: Post)
  layout: |
    ┌───────────────────────────────┐
    │ [toggle-view]        [+ Post] │
    ├───────────────────────────────┤
    │ gallery: Masonry of PostCards  │
    │   -or-                        │
    │ instructions: markdown Surface │
    └───────────────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component PostArticle
  desc: >
    Article surface for a Post (AppSurface.object(Article, Post)). The
    outline document renders on top (markdown Surface); a toolbar
    toggle-group has one tab per Draft plus a `+` new-draft action, a
    Publish action (invokes op:PublishDraft) and an Import action (invokes
    op:ImportDrafts) — both disabled until a service:PublisherService is
    contributed AND a Connection whose access-token source matches it
    exists in the same space. The selected Draft's body renders below
    (markdown Surface).
  props:
    role: string
    attendableId: string
    subject: Post
  state:
    selectedDraftIndex: number       # defaults to drafts.length - 1
  actions:
    selectDraft(index: number)
    addDraft()
    publish()
    import()
  layout: |
    ┌─────────────────────────────────────────┐
    │ outline (markdown Surface)                │
    ├─────────────────────────────────────────┤
    │ [Draft 1] [Draft 2] [+]  [Publish][Import]│
    ├─────────────────────────────────────────┤
    │ selected draft body (markdown Surface)    │
    └─────────────────────────────────────────┘
```

```mdl
component PostCard
  desc: >
    Summary tile for a Post, rendered as a Masonry Tile in
    PublicationArticle's gallery view. Reactive to the passed Post via
    useObject.
  props:
    post: Post
    onClick?: () => void
  layout: |
    ┌────────────────────────┐
    │ [icon]  title           │
    │ summary excerpt         │
    │ [stack-icon]  N drafts  │
    └────────────────────────┘
```

## Services

```mdl
service PublisherService
  desc: >
    Provider-agnostic publishing backend contract. Implemented by a
    provider plugin (e.g. plugin-typefully) and contributed under
    BloggerCapabilities.PublisherService; every op:PublishDraft /
    op:ImportDrafts / op:UnpublishDraft invocation resolves one contribution
    via Capability.getAll. Identity fields: `id` (capability id), `label`
    (display name), `source` (matches AccessToken.source, e.g.
    "typefully.com"). Every method takes a Ref<Connection> — the
    provider-neutral credential handle; token resolution stays entirely in
    the implementing plugin.
  loading: lazy
  ops:
    listDrafts(connection: Ref<Connection>) → PublisherDraft[]
    getDraft(connection: Ref<Connection>, id: string) → PublisherDraft
    createDraft(connection: Ref<Connection>, input: PublisherDraftInput) → PublisherDraft
    updateDraft(connection: Ref<Connection>, id: string, input: PublisherDraftInput) → PublisherDraft
    deleteDraft(connection: Ref<Connection>, id: string) → void
  errors:
    PublisherError: publish/import/unpublish failed against the remote backend
    MissingCredentialError: the service's credentials (e.g. Connection's access token) are missing
```

## Operations

```mdl
op AddPublication
  desc: >
    Creates a new Publication (with an empty instructions document and no
    posts) and files it under `target`.
  input:
    name?: string
    target: Database | Collection
  output: Ref<Publication>
  effects: [echo:write]
```

```mdl
op AddPost
  desc: >
    Creates a new Post (an outline plus one initial Draft labelled
    "Draft 1") and appends it to `publication.posts`, also filing it under
    `target`.
  input:
    publication: Ref<Publication>
    name?: string
    createdAt?: string              # ISO 8601 timestamp for the initial draft
    target: Database | Collection
  output: Ref<Post>
  effects: [echo:write]
```

```mdl
op AddDraft
  desc: >
    Creates a new Draft (wrapping a fresh markdown document, labelled
    "Draft N" where N = post.drafts.length + 1) and appends it to
    `post.drafts`.
  input:
    post: Ref<Post>
    createdAt?: string
  output: Ref<Draft>
  effects: [echo:write]
```

```mdl
op PublishDraft
  desc: >
    Pushes a Draft's current body to its publisher: createDraft on first
    publish, otherwise updateDraft on the remote copy it is already linked
    to (tracked by a foreign key keyed by the publisher's `source`). Stamps
    (or refreshes) the foreign key with the result id.
  input:
    draft: Ref<Draft>
    connection: Ref<Connection>
    publisherId?: string            # selects a contributed service by id; defaults to the first available
  output: Ref<Draft>
  errors:
    PublisherError: no publisher configured, or the remote call failed
  effects: [echo:write]
  requires: [PublisherService]
  note: >
    Resolves via Capability.getAll(BloggerCapabilities.PublisherService),
    preferring publisherId when given.
```

```mdl
op ImportDrafts
  desc: >
    Pulls a publisher's remote drafts not yet linked to a local Draft
    (dedup by foreign key on `service.source`), creating one local Draft
    per new remote draft (body fetched via getDraft) and appending it to
    `post.drafts`.
  input:
    post: Ref<Post>
    connection: Ref<Connection>
    publisherId?: string
  output: Ref<Post>
  errors:
    PublisherError: no publisher configured, or the remote call failed
  effects: [echo:write]
  requires: [PublisherService]
```

```mdl
op UnpublishDraft
  desc: >
    Deletes a Draft's remote copy (if linked) from its publisher and
    clears the foreign key. No-op when the Draft was never linked.
  input:
    draft: Ref<Draft>
    connection: Ref<Connection>
    publisherId?: string
  output: Ref<Draft>
  errors:
    PublisherError: no publisher configured, or the remote call failed
  effects: [echo:write]
  requires: [PublisherService]
```

## Features

```mdl
feat F-1: Publications Root

  req F-1.1: A global top-level "Publications" branch node is contributed on the app-graph root, sourced from the personal space's Publication objects.
  req F-1.2: "+ Publication" on the Publications root invokes op:AddPublication targeting the personal space's database.
  req F-1.3: Each Publication node expands to its Post children, with a "+ Post" action invoking op:AddPost.
```

```mdl
feat F-2: Publication Authoring

  req F-2.1: component:PublicationArticle defaults to the gallery view: a Masonry grid of component:PostCard, one per Post.
  req F-2.2: Toggling the toolbar view swaps to the instructions view — the Publication's shared instructions document, rendered via the markdown article Surface.
  req F-2.3: "+ Post" in the toolbar invokes op:AddPost against the open Publication.
```

```mdl
feat F-3: Post Drafting and Versions

  req F-3.1: op:AddPost creates a Post with an outline document and one initial Draft labelled "Draft 1".
  req F-3.2: component:PostArticle shows the outline on top, a toggle-group tab per Draft, and the selected Draft's body below; the newest Draft is selected by default.
  req F-3.3: The "+" draft action invokes op:AddDraft and selects the newly created Draft.
```

```mdl
feat F-4: Comments on Drafts

  req F-4.1: Every Draft's `content` is a Markdown.Document, so comments anchor to it automatically via the AnchoredTo relation (plugin-comments) — no blogger-specific wiring.
```

```mdl
feat F-5: Agent Instructions per Publication

  req F-5.1: `Publication.instructions` is a Markdown.Document the author edits directly, carrying the base instructions the assistant agent reads for that Publication. Agent consumption of these instructions is Phase 2 and is NOT built here.
```

```mdl
feat F-6: Push/Pull Sync via Foreign Keys

  req F-6.1: op:PublishDraft creates the remote draft on first publish (no foreign key present for the publisher's source) and updates it thereafter (foreign key present); the Draft's foreign key is refreshed with the result id in both cases.
  req F-6.2: op:ImportDrafts skips remote drafts already linked to a local Draft (matched by foreign key on `service.source`) and creates a local Draft (body via getDraft) for every unlinked one.
  req F-6.3: op:UnpublishDraft deletes the remote draft and clears the foreign key when the Draft is linked; no-op otherwise.
  req F-6.4: The Publish/Import actions in component:PostArticle are disabled until a service:PublisherService is contributed AND a Connection whose access-token source matches it exists in the same space.
```

## Acceptance

```mdl
test T-1: AddPublication persists an empty Publication
  given: a database db
  when: op:AddPublication invoked with { name: "My Blog", target: db }
  then:
    - Publication.name === "My Blog"; Publication.posts === []
    - Publication.instructions resolves to an empty Markdown.Document
    - Publication is queryable from db via Filter.type(Publication)
```

```mdl
test T-2: AddPost creates outline + one initial draft
  given: a persisted Publication and a target Collection
  when: op:AddPost invoked with { publication, name: "Hello World", target }
  then:
    - publication.posts gains a ref resolving to the new Post
    - Post.outline resolves to an empty Markdown.Document
    - post.drafts has length 1; its Draft.label === "Draft 1"
    - Post is filed under `target` (Collection.objects)
```

```mdl
test T-3: AddDraft appends and labels sequentially
  given: a Post with one existing Draft ("Draft 1")
  when: op:AddDraft invoked with { post, createdAt: "2026-07-11T00:00:00Z" }
  then:
    - post.drafts has length 2
    - new Draft.label === "Draft 2"; Draft.createdAt === "2026-07-11T00:00:00Z"
    - new Draft is queryable from db via Filter.type(Draft)
```

```mdl
test T-4: PublishDraft creates on first publish
  given: an unlinked Draft, a stub PublisherService
  when: op:PublishDraft invoked
  then:
    - service.createDraft called (service.updateDraft NOT called)
    - Draft's foreign key for service.source === the returned remote id
```

```mdl
test T-5: PublishDraft updates when already linked
  given: a Draft already linked to remote id "existing1" for service.source
  when: op:PublishDraft invoked
  then:
    - service.updateDraft called with id "existing1" (service.createDraft NOT called)
    - Draft's foreign key unchanged ("existing1")
```

```mdl
test T-6: ImportDrafts dedups by foreign key
  given: a Post whose one Draft is linked to remote id "x1"; service.listDrafts returns ["x1", "x2"]
  when: op:ImportDrafts invoked
  then:
    - only "x2" (unlinked) is imported: one new Draft appended, content === getDraft("x2").text
    - service.createDraft / service.updateDraft are never called
    - the new Draft's foreign key for service.source === "x2"
```

```mdl
test T-7: UnpublishDraft clears the foreign key
  given: a Draft linked to remote id "new1"
  when: op:UnpublishDraft invoked
  then:
    - service.deleteDraft called with "new1"
    - Draft's foreign keys for service.source === []
```

```mdl
test T-8: UnpublishDraft no-ops when never linked
  given: an unlinked Draft
  when: op:UnpublishDraft invoked
  then: service.deleteDraft is never called
```

## Design Notes

- **Navtree sourcing (deferred).** The Publications root sources its children
  from the personal space only (`AppSpace.getPersonalSpace`), not an
  all-spaces aggregation. The graph-builder connector isolates this as a
  single seam (`getPublications`) so the choice can be widened later without
  touching the rest of the shape.
- **Connection selection (deferred).** component:PostArticle resolves the
  first contributed service:PublisherService and the first Connection in the
  space whose linked AccessToken's `source` matches it — there is no
  publisher/connection picker UI yet. `op:PublishDraft` /
  `op:ImportDrafts` / `op:UnpublishDraft` already take an explicit
  `connection` ref, so a picker is additive.
- Phase 2 (agent skills/operations for ideate/draft/publish) is out of scope
  for this spec.

---

## Appendix: Extension Definitions

Extension block types used in this document are defined below using
the core `ext` primitive — the only construct the base language provides.

```mdl
ext type
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.type@1.0
  desc: A named data structure with typed fields and optional literals.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    fields?: FieldMap        # name[?]: TypeExpr  (# inline comment)
    literals?: UnionList     # a | b | c
    extends?: TypeRef[]
```

```mdl
ext feat
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.feat@1.0
  desc: A named feature grouping one or more requirements.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    req: RequirementList
  nesting: self              # feat blocks may contain feat blocks
```

```mdl
ext test
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.test@1.0
  desc: An acceptance scenario expressed as given / when / then steps.
  fields:
    given?: Step | Step[]
    when?: Step | Step[]
    then: Step | Step[]
    tags?: TagList
```

```mdl
ext component
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.component@1.0
  desc: A UI component with props, internal state, slots, actions, and events.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    props?: FieldMap            # external inputs (immutable inside component)
    state?: FieldMap            # internal reactive state
    slots?: FieldMap            # named ReactNode injection points
    actions?: ActionMap         # methods the component exposes or handles
    emits?: EventMap            # events the component raises to its parent
    layout?: CodeBlock          # ASCII sketch of visual structure (non-normative)
```

```mdl
ext op
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.op@1.0
  desc: |
    A named operation with typed inputs, outputs, and declared errors.
    Pure ops have no effects or requires. Effectful ops declare both.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    input?: FieldMap            # named input parameters
    output?: TypeExpr           # return type
    errors?: ErrorMap           # name: Prose  (when this error occurs)
    effects?: EffectList        # echo:read | echo:write | http | fs | ...
    requires?: ServiceList      # injected service dependencies
    note?: Prose                # implementation guidance (non-normative)
```

```mdl
ext service
  uri: org.dxos.mdl.service@1.0
  desc: An external or system-level dependency providing named operations.
  fields:
    desc?: Prose
    loading?: eager | lazy
    ops?: OpMap                 # name(params) → ReturnType
    errors?: ErrorMap
    note?: Prose
```
